benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from account

covered: Valid deletion paths: TC01, TC02, TC04 validate successful removal of custom fields in typical and edge cases.

Header/auth/validation coverage: Tests verify required header presence (TC07), unauthorized access (TC10), invalid accountId (TC05), and invalid customField IDs (TC08, TC19), including edge-case parameter handling (TC09).
Concurrency and performance: TC16 executes high-concurrency deletes to validate throughput and completion within acceptable time.
Post-deletion verification: Tests validate system state via GET after deletions (TC01, TC04).
Edge-case coverage: Duplicates (TC14), max fields (TC13), partial population (TC18), and regression case (TC15) are exercised.
gaps: Soft deletes: No tests validating a soft-delete state or tombstone semantics.
Non-existent resource error path: Deleting a non-existent account expects 204; no explicit test asserting 404/400 error semantics.
GET-side testing: No pagination or caching validation (ETag/Cache-Control) on the list of custom fields.
Rate limiting: No tests covering DELETE rate limiting or throttling.
RBAC breadth: Broader authorization scenarios could be explored beyond missing/invalid header and unauthorized access.
recommendations: Clarify and test non-existent account error paths (e.g., 404) if API semantics require error on missing resources.
Add soft-delete tests if applicable, verifying state or tombstone where deletion is logical rather than physical.
Add GET tests with pagination and caching headers to validate data retrieval behavior after deletions.
Introduce rate-limiting tests to ensure DELETE operations remain robust under bursts of requests.
Expand security tests to cover additional RBAC scenarios and inject vectors beyond current coverage.
